 as autism assistance dogs diabetic alert dogs facilitated guide dogs fasd assistance dogs hearing ear dogs mobility assistance dogs seizure assistance dogs veterans assistance dogs and more there is a lot of work that goes in to prepare these service dogs for the role they play and the miracle they become we thank the team at  paws for ability for the miracles they have done and the joy they have brought in the lives of many so please join me on august th to support  paws for ability and their service dogs shop more to give more thank you for being our partner and believing in us naheed quaisar cofounder and ceo help us spread the word please help us get the word out together we can give ‘ paws for ability’ the support it needs to breed socialize train and place service dogs with children and veterans starting from their inhouse breeding program to final ceremony of a publicly socialized dog they need all the help and support from us ways to share nbsp share it on facebook nbsp tweet it on twitter nbsp tell your friends  family nbsp print and post it at work in  karen shirk was told she was too disabled to receive a service dog she decided to make sure no one else ever had to hear those words  paws for ability is the embodiment of karen’s vision  a nonprofit organization that breeds socializes trains and places service dogs with children and veterans since its inception in   paws has paired over  trained service dogs to people living with a variety of disabilities with a team of  employees and over  volunteers  paws now places over  dogs per year  paws dogs and the humans they love and serve can be found in almost all  statesas well as australia canada germany japan mexico new zealand and switzerland our first priority is always to reunite our youth with healthy functional family for the majority of our kids for whom family is not an option we give them an educational  vocational assessment and help them find a job that suits their skills and interest we offer many services to help from mock interviews  resume writing classes to workshops on basic life skills and healthy relationships dogs trained through  paws meet the criteria for ‘service animals’ as defined by the americans with disabilities act ada these dogs serve in diverse areas • diabetic alert • seizure alert • hearing assistance • autism assistance • mobility assistance • multipurpose assistance • ptsd assistance • assistance for children with fetal alcohol • syndrome disorder fasddrug exposure the  paws journey begins with an inhouse breeding program that produces healthy dogs with the behavioral profile needed to succeed as an assistance animal the dogs are accustomed to human interaction from their first day of life staff and volunteers assist in the whelping rooms and continuously monitor the new litters as soon as the puppies are weaned they are moved to the puppy house this is a popular volunteer opportunity imagine walking into a house full of puppies spending hours playing and cuddling with them puppies soon begin public socialization this is a critical time in a puppy’s development puppies under careful supervision are slowly exposed to various stimuli  crowds grass leashes service dog vests  to acclimate them to life as a service dog they are then moved out of the puppy house and into the care of a puppy raiser some of our dogs enter a traditional foster home setting with volunteers who commit not only to the raising of a puppy that is not their own but also to the challenging and rewarding task of exposing that puppy to the widest possible number of socialization opportunities other dogs spend time at one of four ohio correctional facilities we use for foursix weeks learning basic obedience potty training and crate training by vetted inmates who attend a weekly class with a  paws trainer other puppies join the  paws university program currently  paws partners with  universities within a threehour radius of the facility student organizations are established on these campuses to foster several dogs at a time often in teams that allow for greater diversity in the puppies’ experiences college campuses provide an enormous variety of socialization opportunities from classroom environments important for those dogs who will serve a schoolaged child to sporting events many of our  paws dogs have walked with their college fosters across the stage as the students receive their diplomas the students love the chance to share this important achievement with their foster pup who helped make their college experience so memorable and rewarding around one year of age the professional training staff at  paws evaluate each dog to determine if the dog meets the strict criteria necessary to continue in advanced training some dogs are not selected for advanced training at this point they are made available for adoption the  paws team likes to call these dogs the ‘fabulous flunkies’  loving dogs who fell just short of the narrow standards needed for service doghood many happy dog owners have found their perfect companion  and many happy dogs have found ‘forever homes’  through the adoption program the dogs who continue in the advanced training program begin rigorous instruction with the training staff it is here the dog is trained for the specific task that will serve their ‘match’  the child or veteran who has been on their own journey while their service dog in training has been working so hard the dog you see is only half the team while the dog has been learning everything from ‘sit’ to ‘leave it’ to the intricate training required to alert a potential medical crisis the recipient of the dog has been busy service dogs are not covered by most insurance plans and a fully trained service dog through  paws costs between  families who have been approved by  paws are asked to pay or fundraise  except veterans who are completely free  paws provides promotional assistance and training during the fundraising process most families have multiple events during their fundraising period some families raise the required amount others find they raise enough money to cover the full cost of the dog excess funds are administered through  paws to families who may have fallen short during the fundraising process adhering to one of the most fundamental principles of the  paws mission no one approved through the  paws application process is denied because of the inability to pay the final steps of the journey are made together by the child or veteran with disabilities and the service dog who has been trained as their companion the final two weeks of training show the recipient how to work with and begin life with a new service dog during this time the bonding process begins  the start of a lifetime partnership between human and canine a graduation ceremony at the end of the training allows the puppy raisers and the new service dog families to celebrate the successful completion of the training process connecting individuals who were impacted by the raising and training of these dogs httpwwwpawsforabilityorg covenant house new orleans was founded on the edge of the french quarter  years ago to provide a safe haven for homeless runaway and atrisk youth ages  and under we have provided over  kids with food shelter clothing medical care educational and vocational support individual and family counseling job readiness and placement short  longterm housing life skills and more the vast majority of our youth have endured physical andor sexual abuse and have also experienced the violence of the streets our counselors estimate  suffer from some form of traumatic stress disorder tulane’s cowen institute estimates there are  atrisk youth in our community our first priority is always to reunite our youth with healthy functional family for the majority of our kids for whom family is not an option we give them an educational  vocational assessment and help them find a job that suits their skills and interest httpwwwcovenanthousenoorg soldiers’ angels provides aid and comfort to the men and women of the united states army marines navy air force coast guard and their families and a growing veteran population soldiers’ angels was established in  by the mother of a son who was deployed to iraq she began sending care packages to her son and was then asked to not only send more care packages to many more deployed but to also assist with other needs september th was a catalyst that inspired americans to support the military and help out any way they could soldiers’ angels was created as an opportunity for them to provide that support with care packages handsewn blankets letters cards and other items from ‘home’ in just  years since this small beginning of sending care packages soldiers’ angels has grown to over  programs with over  volunteers nationwide most of the programs and services offered by soldiers’ angels are performed by volunteers who work tirelessly supporting our nation’s veterans wounded warriors deployed service members and their families httpwwwsoldiersangelsorg on may th hpfy donated  of the day’s sales to ‘asha for education’ asha for education took roots in  when a group of students including deepak gupta sandeep pandey and vjp srivatsavoy from the university of berkeley ca got together and discussed ways to bring about a socioeconomic change in india the group was formed with a belief that education is a requisite to bring about the much needed socio economic change in india it was named ‘asha’ meaning ‘hope’ since then asha for education has grown via its chapters and today has more than  chapters worldwide asha for education is a c organization in the us each year our work touches the lives of several thousands of children across a few hundreds of projects we have no offices and  of our efforts are driven by unpaid volunteers all donations are tax deductible and we have earned a reputation for sending  of donations to our projects httpwwwashanetorg on april th hpfy donated  of t